members.description: Field title (used in form labels, table column headers etc.)

members.name: type
members.title: Type
members.description: Field data type used in form validations. Examples: "string", "integer", "float", "date", "time", "bool", "array", "email", "random_string". Default: "string"

members.name: default
members.title: Default value
members.description: Default value. For date fields you can use special constant "today", for time fields you can use "now". Also, you can set helper here "{{myHelper}}".

members.name: min
members.title: Min. value
members.description: Minimum value (only for numeric fields)

members.name: max
members.title: Max. value
members.description: Maximum value (only for numeric fields)

members.name: required
members.title: Required
members.description: Is field input required? Default: false

members.name: format
members.title: Format
members.description: Currently used only with data types "date" and "time". Contains date or time format such as "MM/DD/YYYY" or "hh:mm:ss"

members.name: searchable
members.title: Searchable
members.description: Is field searchable? Default: true

members.name: sortable
members.title: Sortable
members.description: Is field sortable? Default: true

members.name: exportable
members.title: Exportable
members.description: If true field will be exported to CSV/JSON (used in dataview component). Default: false

members.name: input
members.title: Input
members.description: Form input control type: "text", "password", "datepicker", "read-only", "textarea", "radio", "checkbox", "select", "crud", "file", "custom"

members.name: input_template
members.title: Input template
members.description: Template for "custom" input field (relative to input file)

members.name: input_group_class
members.title: Input group class
members.description: This CSS class will be added to field input group container in forms.

members.name: input_control_class
members.title: Input control class
members.description: This CSS class will be added to input control in forms.

members.name: input_items
members.title: Input items
members.description: Item list for input type "radio" and "select"

members.name: lookup_query_name
members.title: Lookup query name
members.description: Query name used for form input type "select".

members.name: lookup_query_params
members.title: Lookup query params
members.description: Lookup query params

members.name: lookup_key
members.title: Lookup value field
members.description: Field name from lookup_query used as option value in input type "select". Mandatory field if lookup_query is defined

members.name: lookup_field
members.title: Lookup title field
members.description: Field name from lookup_query used as option title in input type "select". Mandatory field if lookup query is defined

members.name: display_helper
members.title: Display helper
members.description: Helper name used to display value from this field (used in DataView, Forms etc.)

members.name: array_item_type
members.title: Array item type
members.description: If "type" is set to "array" then you can define array item type here. Format is the same as for "type" property.

members.name: crud_fields
members.title: CRUD input fields
members.description: If "array_item_type" is set to "object" then you can define fields for input type "crud".

members.name: crud_insert_title
members.title: CRUD insert title
members.description: For fields with "input": "crud" - insert button and insert form title

members.name: file_collection
members.title: File collection
members.description: For fields with "input": "file". Name of FS.Collection where file is stored. Generator will automatically join this collection with file_collection.

members.name: file_container
members.title: File container field
members.description: For fields with "input": "file". Field name where FS.File object from joined FS.Collection will be stored.

members.name: join_collection
members.title: Join collection
members.description: Collection name to join with. If set then this field acts as foreign key. For generic join don't set this field (see "join_collection_field" instead).

members.name: join_collection_field
members.title: Join collection field
members.description: Used in generic joins only. Field name (from this collection) containing collection name to join with. If set then this field acts as foreign key.

members.name: join_container
members.title: Join container field
members.description: Field name where document from joined collection will be stored

members.name: join_fields
members.title: Join fields
members.description: Field list to fetch from joined collection. Ignored in generic joins.

members.name: show_in_dataview
members.title: Show in dataviews
members.description: If set to "false", field will not be shown in dataview components. Default: true

members.name: show_in_insert_form
members.title: Show in insert forms
members.description: If set to "false", field will not be included in forms with mode "insert". Default: true

members.name: show_in_update_form
members.title: Show in update forms
members.description: If set to "false", field will not be included in forms with mode "update". Default: true

members.name: show_in_read_only_form
members.title: Show in read-only forms
members.description: If set to "false", field will not be included in forms with mode "read_only". Default: true

members.title: Type
members.description: Collection type. Can be "collection" or "file_collection" (FS.Collection). Default: "collection".

members.name: storage_adapters
members.title: Storage adapters
members.description: For collection of type "file_collection": list of CollectionFS storage adapters: "gridfs", "filesystem", "s3" or "dropbox". If not specified, generator will assume "gridfs".

members.name: fields
members.title: Fields
members.description: Field list. Not mandatory, used by components such as form, dataview etc.

members.name: owner_field
members.title: Owner field
members.description: Field name used to store user ID of document owner. Only for apps using user accounts. Value of this field will be automatically set server side by "before.insert" hook.

members.name: roles_allowed_to_read
members.title: Roles allowed to Read
members.description: List of user roles that can subscribe to this collection. You can use special roles "nobody" (nobody can read) and "owner" (only owner/creator can read).

members.name: roles_allowed_to_insert
members.title: Roles allowed to Insert
members.description: List of user roles that can insert documents into this collection. You can use special role "nobody" (nobody can insert).

members.name: roles_allowed_to_update
members.title: Roles allowed to Update
members.description: List of user roles that can update documents. You can use special roles "nobody" (nobody can update) and "owner" (only owner/creator can update).

members.name: roles_allowed_to_delete
members.title: Roles allowed to Delete
members.description: List of user roles that can delete documents. You can use special roles "nobody" (nobody can remove) and "owner" (only owner/creator can remove).

members.name: roles_allowed_to_download
members.title: Roles allowed to Download
members.description: For collection of type "file_collection": List of user roles that can download files. You can use special roles "nobody" (nobody can download) and "owner" (only owner/creator can download).

members.name: before_insert_code
members.title: Before insert code
members.description: Code to be executed before new document is inserted into collection. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc). See meteor-collection-hooks package for more details.

members.name: before_update_code
members.title: Before update code
members.description: Code to be executed before document is updated. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc, fieldNames, modifier, options)

members.name: before_remove_code
members.title: Before remove code
members.description: Code to be executed before document is removed. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc)

members.name: after_insert_code
members.title: After insert code
members.description: Code to be executed after new document is inserted into collection. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc). See meteor-collection-hooks package for more details.

members.name: after_update_code
members.title: After update code
members.description: Code to be executed after document is updated. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc, fieldNames, modifier, options)

members.name: after_remove_code
members.title: After remove code
members.description: Code to be executed after document is removed. Should be only body of a function with args: (userId, doc)

members.name: before_insert_source_file
members.title: Before insert source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed before new document is inserted (relative to input JSON file). See "before_insert_code".

members.name: before_update_source_file
members.title: Before update source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed before document is updated (relative to input JSON file). See "before_update_code".

members.name: before_remove_source_file
members.title: Before remove source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed before document is removed (relative to input JSON file). See "before_remove_code".

members.name: after_insert_source_file
members.title: After insert source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed after new document is inserted (relative to input JSON file). See "after_insert_code".

members.name: after_update_source_file
members.title: After update source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed after document is updated (relative to input JSON file). See "after_update_code".

members.name: after_remove_source_file
members.title: After remove source file
members.description: File that contains code to be executed after document is removed (relative to input JSON file). See "after_remove_code".
